<div class="py-5 text-center">
		<h2>The Followers Count</h2>
		<p class="lead">
				This is a simple horizontal meter that fills as you get more followers.
				Use the following URL syntax:
		</p>
		<div class="highlight">
				<code>/followers/goal/{goal_value}/{caption}</code>
		</div>
</div>

<dl>
		<dt>goal_value</dt>
		<dd>The integer value of the goal number of followers</dd>
		<dt>caption</dt>
		<dd>The caption to display that defines the goal</dd>
</dl>

<h4>Other Parameters</h4>
<p>Other parameters can be passed on the querystring using standard name-value syntax</p>

<dl>
		<dt>width</dt>
		<dd>The width in pixels of the bar</dd>

		<dt>current</dt>
		<dd>A 'current follower count' to use for testing</dd>

		<dt>fontName</dt>
		<dd>An optional font name from <a href="https://fonts.google.com/" target="_blank">Google Fonts</a></dd>

		<dt>bgcolors</dt>
		<dd>A comma separated list of colors/values for the background - ordered left to right.</dd>

		<dt>bgblend</dt>
		<dd>A comma separated list of values between 0 and 1 representing how much of the color should be blended into the next color.</dd>
		<dd>A value of zero means there will be a sharp cutover to the next color.</dd>
		<dd>A value of one means there will be a smooth blend to the next color over the full width of the color section.</dd>
		<dd>As the value increases from 0 (sharp cutover) the amount of blended overlap increases.</dd>

		<dt>Examples</dt>
		<dd>Blended Blue to Green : <a href="/followers/goal/400/Example%20Blue%20to%20Green?width=400&current=377&bgcolors=blue,green&bgblend=1,1">/followers/goal/400/Example%20Blue%20to%20Green?width=400&amp;current=377&amp;bgcolors=blue,green&amp;bgblend=1,1</a></dd>
		<dd>Stepped Blue to Green : <a href="/followers/goal/400/Example%20Blue%20to%20Green?width=400&current=377&bgcolors=blue,green&bgblend=0,0">/followers/goal/400/Example%20Blue%20to%20Green?width=400&amp;current=377&amp;bgcolors=blue,green&amp;bgblend=0,0</a></dd>
		<dd>Smooth step Blue to Green : <a href="/followers/goal/400/Example%20Blue%20to%20Green?width=400&current=377&bgcolors=blue,green&bgblend=0.1,0.1">/followers/goal/400/Example%20Blue%20to%20Green?width=400&amp;current=377&amp;bgcolors=blue,green&amp;bgblend=0.1,0.1</a></dd>
</dl>

<h3>Color Configuration</h3>

<p>
		You can configure the colors of the goal bar by setting the following configuration options in appsettings.json
		OR setting the appropriate environment variable
</p>

<dl>
		<dt>FollowerGoal__EmptyBackgroundColor</dt>
		<dd>Sets the background color of the empty bar</dd>
		<dt>FollowerGoal__EmptyFontColor</dt>
		<dd>Sets the font color of the empty bar</dd>
		<dt>FollowerGoal__FillBackgroundColor</dt>
		<dd>Sets the background color(s) of the filled section of the bar</dd>
		<dt>FollowerGoal__FillFontColor</dt>
		<dd>Sets the font color for the filled section of the bar</dd>
		<dt>FollowerGoal__FillBackgroundColorBlend</dt>
		<dd>Sets the required color blends for the filled section of the bar</dd>
		<dt>FollowerGoal__FontName</dt>
		<dd>Sets an optional Google font name for the caption</dd>
</dl>
